Cooking instructions 

1. Preheat convection oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).
2. Rub chicken with olive oil and spices. Let it sit for half an hour  
#For better results, let it sit 1 hour
3. Cut the chiken in 4 pices 
3. Put the chicken in the oven for 2 hours
4. Let it cool for 25 minutes before serving 
5. Leftovers can be refrigerated for about 2 days
6. Drink it with 2 minutemaid juice boxes
